# ğŸ“‹ Post-Installation Checklist - Proxmox VE 9

## Immediate Actions Required

### ğŸ”„ Browser Cache Management
- [ ] **Clear browser cache** (`Ctrl+Shift+R` or `Ctrl+F5`)
- [ ] **Alternative**: Open private/incognito window
- [ ] **Alternative**: Use different browser temporarily
- [ ] Test web interface functionality after clearing cache

### ğŸ”§ System Verification
- [ ] **Reboot the system** (recommended after repository changes)
- [ ] **Test Proxmox web interface** access and functionality
- [ ] **Verify all services are running** (`systemctl status`)
- [ ] **Check system logs** for any errors (`journalctl -f`)

---

## Cluster Environment Tasks

### ğŸ¢ Multi-Node Clusters Only
If you have **multiple Proxmox nodes** in a cluster:

- [ ] **Run this script on ALL cluster nodes** individually
- [ ] **Verify cluster status**: `pvecm status`
- [ ] **Check node communication**: `pvecm nodes`
- [ ] **Test VM migration** (if applicable)
- [ ] **Verify shared storage** access across all nodes
- [ ] **Check corosync status**: `systemctl status corosync`

### âš ï¸ Cluster Health Verification
```bash
# Check cluster status
pvecm status

# Verify all nodes are online
pvecm nodes

# Check quorum
pvecm expected 1  # Only if you have quorum issues
```

---

## Security Review

### ğŸ”’ Security Audit Tasks
- [ ] **Review SSH authorized_keys**: `cat /root/.ssh/authorized_keys`
- [ ] **Check firewall settings**: `iptables -L` or `ufw status`
- [ ] **Verify user accounts**: `cat /etc/passwd | grep -E "bash|sh"`
- [ ] **Monitor system logs**: `tail -f /var/log/auth.log`
- [ ] **Review active network connections**: `ss -tuln`

### ğŸ”‘ SSH Security
- [ ] **Test SSH key authentication** (if added)
- [ ] **Verify SSH service configuration**: `sshd -T`
- [ ] **Check for failed login attempts**: `grep "Failed password" /var/log/auth.log`
- [ ] **Consider enabling fail2ban**: `apt install fail2ban`

---

## System Performance

### ğŸ“Š Resource Monitoring
- [ ] **Check memory usage**: `free -h`
- [ ] **Monitor CPU usage**: `top` or `htop`
- [ ] **Verify disk space**: `df -h`
- [ ] **Check storage pool status**: `zpool status` (if using ZFS)

### âš¡ High Availability Status
- [ ] **Verify HA services status** (if enabled):
  ```bash
  systemctl status pve-ha-lrm
  systemctl status pve-ha-crm
  systemctl status corosync
  ```
- [ ] **Check HA configuration**: `ha-manager status`

